            called
                <?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101106T104833-0400" content="&quot;"?><em>Sample
                Spaces and
            Events</em>.<?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101106T104836-0400" content="&quot;"?>
            We will then establish the basic methods and principles for finding probabilities of
            events<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101106T104902-0400"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
            which will be organized in two sections:
                <?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101106T104909-0400" content="&quot;"?><em>Equally
                Likely
            Outcomes</em><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101106T104906-0400" content="&quot;"?>
            and
                <?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101106T104913-0400" content="&quot;"?><em>Probability
                Rules</em>.<?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101106T104915-0400" content="&quot;"?>
